SUMMARY:I SPY A BOOK
DESCRIPTION:\n\nI spy with my little eye…  \nIn this session children will learn to find their way around the library through the beloved I Spy game\, a sprinkle of history\, and of course\, stories! This is a morning for young readers to understand their interests\, explore their curiosity\, and find community\, in the friendly and wondrous place that is a library. \n\n\n\nAround the World in 50 Sundays is a journey that begins\, not with a ticket\, but with opening a book. In a city like Bangalore where families are always in motion\, the BIC Library hopes to offer stillness and a quiet\, welcoming space for both parents and children where reading becomes a shared experience. \nEvery Sunday\, we open our doors to invite you into a library that listens; building a rhythm of return\, a habit of joy and a new community bound not just by books\, but by the weekly ritual of reading together. \nWe welcome your ideas and input. If you have suggestions for children’s events or activities that align with this vision\, we’d love to hear from you. Please reach out to us at library@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org \nSupported by:\n \n\n\n\nA Morning of Book Spotting Adventures with Friends\nFor Ages 6-9\nRSVPs closed. Thank you for your interest.\n*Facilitator*: Shravanthi Venkatesh\n*Event Categories*: Around the World in 50 Sundays
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/i-spy-a-book/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Around the World in 50 Sundays
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Thumbnail-3-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
