SUMMARY:Structure and Light
DESCRIPTION:Exhibition Opening: 6:30pm\, Fri\, 31 Jul\nExhibition Timings: 11am – 9pm | Fri\, 31 Jul – Mon\, 3 Aug\nExhibition on show until: 6:30pm | Mon\, 3 Aug \nWalkthroughs:\n6:30pm | Fri\, 31 Jul\n2pm & 8pm | Sat\, 1 Aug\n4pm & 6pm | Sun\, 2 Aug\n5pm | Mon\, 3 Aug \nWorkshop: Architectural Photography | 4pm – 7pm | Sat\, 1 Aug \nPanel Discussion: Design and the Lens | 11:30am – 1pm | Sun\, 2 Aug \nStructure and Light is an exhibition of architectural photography and film. In celebration of twenty years of BRS Sreenag’s practice\, the works on display demonstrate his approach to architectural photography\, and his use of natural light to highlight the structure’s design. Architectural films will be on display\, along with a behind-the-scene look at how they were made. \nIn collaboration with: \n \nSreenag Pictures is an award-winning architectural imagery practice based in India\, which celebrated twenty years in 2025. Founded by BRS Sreenag\, when architectural photography was a fraction of the industry it is today\, Sreenag Pictures has grown into an experienced team\, offering architects\, developers\, and designers a planning-oriented\, design-focused approach to photography. \nVenue: Gallery\n\n\nAn Exhibition of Architectural Photography and Film\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdOxDm6tNrRK36JLUrjU9xlJs5DLy1ffS7SkWePe3cnD4AiCw/viewform?usp=pp_url)\n*Event Categories*: Architecture\, Photography\, Visual Arts
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/structure-and-light/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Architecture,Photography,Visual Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Thumbnail-6.jpg
END:VEVENT
